**Missing `ServicePort.Protocol` normalization — spurious Service updates when Protocol is omitted**

`ServiceSpecDefaults` normalizes spec-level fields (`Type`, `SessionAffinity`, `InternalTrafficPolicy`) but omits port-level defaults. The Kubernetes API server defaults each `ServicePort.Protocol` to `"TCP"` when the field is unset. A caller that constructs a Service with `ServicePort{Port: 80}` (no explicit Protocol) will have `newSpec.Ports[i].Protocol == ""` after `ServiceSpecDefaults`, while `existingSpec.Ports[i].Protocol == "TCP"`. Because `reflect.DeepEqual` is used for string fields, `"" != "TCP"` — the `apiequality.Semantic.DeepEqual` guard in `EnsureService` returns `false` and `c.Update` is called on every reconcile.

All tests in `deployment_test.go` explicitly set `Protocol: corev1.ProtocolTCP`, so this gap is not exercised.

Add port Protocol normalization:

```suggestion
func ServiceSpecDefaults(spec *corev1.ServiceSpec) {
	if spec.Type == "" {
		spec.Type = corev1.ServiceTypeClusterIP
	}
	if spec.SessionAffinity == "" {
		spec.SessionAffinity = corev1.ServiceAffinityNone
	}
	if spec.InternalTrafficPolicy == nil {
		cluster := corev1.ServiceInternalTrafficPolicyCluster
		spec.InternalTrafficPolicy = &cluster
	}
	for i := range spec.Ports {
		if spec.Ports[i].Protocol == "" {
			spec.Ports[i].Protocol = corev1.ProtocolTCP
		}
	}
}
```

